This topic describes how you can log into <%= vars.ops_manager_first %> for the first time after deploying <%= vars.ops_manager %>. It also describes how you can configure the <%= vars.ops_manager %> default authentication with either SAML, LDAP, or internal authentication.

## <a id='overview'></a> About login and authentication methods

When you have a new installation of <%= vars.ops_manager %>, you choose the default authentication and login method.

When you log in for the first time, you go to the fully qualified domain name (FQDN) in your web browser. You configure the FQDN when you first deploy <%= vars.ops_manager %>. To log in, see [Log In to <%= vars.ops_manager %> For the First Time](#login-first-time).

Your login method and authentication choices are:

* **[Internal Authentication](#internal):** <%= vars.ops_manager %> maintains and manages your user database.

* **[SAML Identity Provider](#saml2):** An external identity server maintains your user database.

* **[LDAP Server](#ldap):** An external identity server maintains your user database.

* **[OIDC Identity Provider](#oidc):** An external identity server maintains your user database.

## <a id='login-first-time'></a> Log in to <%= vars.ops_manager %> for the first time

To log in to <%= vars.ops_manager %> for the first time with a new <%= vars.ops_manager %> deployment:

1. In a web browser, go to <%= vars.ops_manager %> using your FQDN. You set your FQDN when you configure <%= vars.ops_manager %> before deployment.

1. When <%= vars.ops_manager %> starts for the first time, choose one of the following procedures:
    * [Internal Authentication](#internal)
    * [SAML Identity Provider](#saml2)
    * [LDAP Server](#ldap)


## <a id='internal'></a> Log in to <%= vars.ops_manager %> with internal authentication

To set up internal authentication that <%= vars.ops_manager %> maintains:

1.  When redirected to the **Internal Authentication** page:
    * Enter a **Username**, **Password**, and **Password confirmation** to create an Admin user.
    * Enter a **Decryption passphrase** and the **Decryption passphrase confirmation**. This passphrase encrypts the <%= vars.ops_manager %> datastore and is not recoverable.
    * If you are using an **HTTP proxy** or **HTTPS proxy**, follow the instructions in [Configuring Proxy Settings for the BOSH CPI](./install/pcf-director-proxy-settings.html.md.erb).
    * Read the **End User License Agreement**, and select the check box to accept the terms.
    * Click **Setup Authentication**.

1. Log in to <%= vars.ops_manager %> with the Admin username and password you created in the previous step.

